'''Américo Castilla''' is an Argentinian artist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.macromuseo.org.ar/coleccion/artista/c/castilla_americo.html |title=m a c r o m u s e o |publisher=Macromuseo.org.ar |date= |accessdate=2015-09-20}}</ref> who is the president and founder of [[Fundación TyPA]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Patricia Rodón |url=http://www.mdzol.com/entrevista/75251-los-museos-de-mendoza-adolecen-de-fragilidad-institucional/ |title="Los museos de Mendoza adolecen de fragilidad institucional" - MDZ Online |publisher=Mdzol.com |date=2008-10-07 |accessdate=2015-09-20}}</ref> Castilla qualified as a lawyer. He was director of the cultural program of [[Fundación Antorchas]] from 1992 to 2003, national director of heritage and museums of Argentina from 2003 to 2007, and director of the [[National Museum of Fine Arts in Buenos Aires]] from 2005 to 2007. Castilla also teaches at the [[National University of La Plata]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://elmuseoreimaginado.com/en/disertante/americo-castilla-argentina/ |title=Américo Castilla / Argentina &#124; El Museo Reimaginado - SEPTEMBER 2 – 4 , 2015 @ BUENOS AIRES, ARGENTINA |publisher=El Museo Reimaginado |date=2014-06-20 |accessdate=2015-09-20}}</ref>
