[[File:Freiburg im Breisgau, Deutschland, Colombischlössle.jpg|300px|thumbnail|right|Colombischlössle Museum]]
The '''Colombischlössle Archeological Museum''' is a [[museum]] in [[Freiburg im Breisgau]] in southwest [[Germany]] which features the prehistoric  inheritance of the High and Upper Rhine. It was founded as the Museum of Prehistory and Early History in 1983. The focus of the museum is on the human development of the [[High Rhine|High]] and [[upper Rhine]] from the [[Paleolithic|Paleolithic Age]] to the [[Early Middle Ages]].

== References ==
* Hilde Hiller: ''20 Jahre Museum für Ur- und Frühgeschichte im Colombischlössle''. Museum für Ur- und Frühgeschichte, Freiburg, (Breisgau) 2003.


