{{refimprove|date=July 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use British English|date=August 2015}} [[File:Great Russell Street Bloomsbury.JPG|thumb|right|Great Russell Street viewed from its junction with Bloomsbury Street]] '''Great Russell Street''' is a street in [[Bloomsbury, London|Bloomsbury]], London, best known for being the location of the [[British Museum]]. It runs between [[Tottenham Court Road]] (part of the [[A400 road (Great Britain)|A400 route]]) in the west, and [[Southampton Row]] (part of the A4200 route) in the east. It is one-way only (eastbound) between its western origin at Tottenham Court Road and Bloomsbury Street.
The headquarters of the [[Trades Union Congress]] is located at Nos. 23-28 ([[Congress House]]). The street is also the home of the Contemporary Ceramics Centre, the gallery for the Craft Potters Association of Great Britain, as well as the [[High Commission of Barbados, London|High Commission of Barbados]] to the United Kingdom.
== Famous residents == [[File:Jarndyce Booksellers, 46 Great Russell Street, Feb 2016 02.jpg|thumb|Jarndyce Booksellers, 46 Great Russell Street]] {{sources|section|date=September 2018}}
Great Russell Street has had a number of notable residents, especially during the [[Victorian era]], including: * [[Charles Dickens]] (1812&ndash;1870), novelist, lived at No. 14. * [[W. H. Davies]] (1871&ndash;1940), poet and writer, lived at No. 14 (1916&ndash;22).<ref>Waters, B. (ed.) (1951), ''The Essential W. H. Davies'', London: [[Jonathan Cape]], (Introduction: W. H. Davies, Man and Poet, pp. 9–20)</ref> * [[Randolph Caldecott]] (1846&ndash;1886), illustrator, lived at No. 46. * [[Thomas Henry Wyatt]] (1807&ndash;1880), architect, lived at No. 77. * [[Percy Bysshe Shelley]] (1792&ndash;1822), poet, lodged at No. 119 (February-March, 1818).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bieri|first1=James|title=Percy Bysshe Shelley: A Biography : Exile of Unfulfilled Renown, 1816-1822|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=TPfPWaPD-CcC&pg=PA57|publisher=University of Delaware Press|accessdate=31 October 2017|page=57|language=en|date=2005}}</ref>
== See also == Adjoining streets: * [[Bloomsbury Square]] * [[Museum Street]] Nearby: * [[The Cartoon Museum]] * [[St. George's, Bloomsbury|St. George's church]] * [[Dominion Theatre]]
